The League Championship Algorithm (LCA) is a sport-inspired optimization algorithm that has been widely used in solving optimization problems and real-world applications. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category, which deals with optimization algorithms and their applications. Additionally, the LCA has shown great potentials in solving non-deterministic polynomial time (NP-complete) problems, which makes it relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The algorithm also involves data structures and algorithms, which makes it relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Furthermore, the LCA has been used in machine learning and statistical modeling, which makes it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the LCA has been applied in control systems and robotics, which makes it relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
